2 unit Chicken Breasts
454 g Broccoli, florets
1 tbsp BBQ Seasoning
56 g Salad Topping Mix
4 tbsp Mayonnaise
3 tbsp Sour Cream
56 g Yellow Onion
7 g Dill
2 tbsp BBQ Sauce
113 g Canned Corn
1.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt and Pepper*

Before starting, preheat your broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce. Finely chop half the dill (use all for 4 ppl). Peel, halve, then cut half the onion (whole onion for 4 ppl) into 1/4-inch pieces (whole onion for 4 ppl). Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces. Drain, then rinse corn. Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Carefully slice each chicken breast in half, parallel to the cutting board. Add chicken and BBQ Seasoning to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.  Set aside.

Add broccoli, onions, half the corn (use all for 4 ppl) and 1 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl) to a foil-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to combine. Broil in the middle of the oven until broccoli is golden-brown and tender, 4-5 min.

While veggies broil, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. When hot, add 1/2 tbsp oil (dbl for 4 ppl), then chicken. Sear until golden-brown, 2-3 min per side. (TIP: It's okay if the chicken doesn't cook all the way through in this step!)

Transfer chicken to another foil-lined baking sheet. Brush half the BBQ sauce (all for 4 ppl) over tops of chicken. Broil in the middle of the oven until cooked through, 5-6 min.\*\*

While chicken broils, stir together mayo, sour cream and dill in a large bowl. Add broiled veggies and salad topping mix. Stir to coat.

Divide BBQ chicken and broccoli salad between plates.